=Summary=

"LePoire (2009: 217) offers an interesting frame on this problem by arguing for viewing history as a complex adaptive process in which succeeding phases of energy intensification over time have led to greater complexity. He thinks the succeeding phases are recognizable '''in five-fold expansions in energy intensity''' and dates them as follows: 

- civilization (3000 BCE–400 CE), 

- commerce (700–1720), 

- industrialization (1720–1950), and 

- knowledge-based (1950–?)." 

